      "type": "feature",
      "system": {
        "description": {
          "value": "<p>Harald is incapable of speaking a direct falsehood. He may keep secrets, deflect, or remain silent — but he will never state something he knows to be false. Creatures who spend time with him may make an easy Intuition test to sense his sincerity. He will not deny the existence of the cipher packet, the mission, or Gragnir if asked directly.</p>",
          "director": "<p>Director note: If a hero asks Harald a direct yes/no question, he answers truthfully even if the answer is uncomfortable. He can say 'I cannot tell you that' but cannot say 'No' when the answer is 'Yes.'</p>"
        },
        "source": {
          "book": "Svellheim Campaign (Era of Embers)",
          "page": "Beat 03",
          "license": ""
        },
        "_dsid": "harald-does-not-lie",
