        "lastModifiedBy": null
      },
      "type": "feature",
      "system": {
        "description": {
          "value": "<p>Once per scene, Harald can invoke the authority of the Cold Iron Crown. He makes a Presence test against one creature who respects legitimate authority. On a tier 2+ result, that creature must truthfully answer one yes-or-no question or comply with a simple lawful order.</p>",
          "director": "<p>Director note: This works on Chainwardens, loyal Svellheim citizens, and anyone who respects crown authority. It does not work on Pale Maw cultists, Grafvitnir agents, or those who have renounced their oaths.</p>"
        },
        "source": {
          "book": "Svellheim Campaign (Era of Embers)",
          "page": "Beat 03",
          "license": ""
        },
